node.statement: CASE 1b - Assume g_1(B) = B AND g_2(B) is not equal to B. FROM CASE 1 SETUP (1.2): B contains supp(g_1) = {1, 3, 4, 6, a_1, ..., a_n}. EXPLICIT CONTENTS: B contains {1, 3, 4, 6, a_1, ..., a_n}. ANALYSIS OF g_2: Since g_2(B) is not equal to B, and 1 is in B intersect supp(g_2), by block property g_2(B) is disjoint from B. g_2 = (1 2 4 5 b_1 ... b_k) maps: g_2(1) = 2, g_2(4) = 5. Since 1, 4 are in B, we have 2, 5 are in g_2(B). Also g_2(B) intersect B = empty. EXPLICIT CONTENTS: g_2(B) contains {2, 5} at minimum.
